This paper is about depth estimation from monocular images, which is a common problem in computer vision. The paper proposes a method that can predict high-quality depth up to an affine transformation, which is a challenging task. The paper also introduces a new dataset called DiverseDepth, which is large-scale and diverse, and can be used to train the proposed method effectively. Given these characteristics, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Other likely sub-categories include cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.GR (Graphics), and cs.RO (Robotics).
